        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks (save some leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Stir the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> and juice of half your <strong>lime[s]</strong> through the cooked rice – this is your <strong>meat-free mince keema</strong></p><p>Taste for seasoning, adding more <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> if needed</p><p>Chop the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into wedges</p>",
